@Julia if I were doing what you are trying to do, I would work backwards in the recipe. It looks like you need an extra half hour or so for the grapes, so you should calculate how long it will take to roast a boneless piece of lamb like you have. 

Based on that, figure out when you have to do the steps where you reduce the sauce and add the grapes in and such. 

If you have a trusted butcher in your area, you could show them the recipe and ask them for advice as well.

@Scott I recently returned from a wonderful trip to Morocco and had my first taste of date molasses. It is delicious, and is nothing like  molasses at all. It was served topping yogurt, fresh fruit, breakfast breads and pastries. I think it would be delicious on hot cereals like oatmeal and even on cold cereals. Grape nuts comes to mind. It could add depth and interest to Brussel sprouts, winter squashes or sweet potatoes. Try it, you’ll like it. It will fit nicely in your pantry, next to the honey and maple syrup. 
Don’t even get me started on pomegranate molasses. Amazing!  
Happy holidays.

